# 🏛️ Architecture Rules

## App Structure

- SPA built with Vite + React + TypeScript; routes via React Router v6.
- Three-layer components:
  - `pages/`: route-level screens.
  - `components/studyflow/`: domain features (timers, summaries, YouTube).
  - `components/ui/`: shadcn-ui primitives.
- Context-driven state: `StudyFlowContext` handles sessions, settings, logs.
- Persistence: browser `localStorage` via `lib/storage.ts` (no backend).

## State & Data Flow

- Use Context API for global state; `useState` for local UI state.
- Flow: User Action → Context Method → Storage → State Update → UI.
- No external state libs (Redux/Zustand/etc.).
- Log sessions and settings through storage helpers only.

## Routing

- Define routes in `App.tsx` within `pages/`.
- Guard/redirect with `useEffect` in pages (e.g., redirect idle sessions to `/`).

## Files & Modules

- One component per file; file name = component name (PascalCase).
- Keep business logic in context/hooks, not UI primitives.
- Utilities stay pure in `lib/`; types live in `types/studyflow.ts`.

## Dependencies

- Allowed: React, React Router, shadcn-ui/Radix, Tailwind, React Query, date-fns, zod, lucide.
- Avoid: external state libs, CSS-in-JS, heavy UI frameworks (MUI/AntD/Chakra).
